Honestly, I have worked
in the service industry,

250
00:12:12,083 --> 00:12:13,375
but nothing like this.

251
00:12:13,458 --> 00:12:14,666
That's enough about me.

252
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:16,291
Have you been a moustache
man for long, or...?

253
00:12:16,375 --> 00:12:22,916
[chattering]

254
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,250
This is goin' a lot better
than I thought it would.

255
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:27,333
[FEMALE 223C screams]

256
00:12:27,416 --> 00:12:28,708
[LUCY, ERZA gasp]

257
00:12:28,791 --> 00:12:29,875
--[FEMALE 223C whimpers]
--Hey. Could ya stop shakin'

258
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:31,291
real quick and
give us some advice?

259
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:32,666
Natsu. Look around.

260
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:34,541
Leave her alone!
Who do you think you are?

261
00:12:34,625 --> 00:12:36,750
Someone above the
"no pets" rule, it seems.

262
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:39,000
He is not my pet!
And his name's Kemo-Kemo!

263
00:12:39,083 --> 00:12:40,958
Whatever it is,
it's totally grotesque.

264
00:12:41,041 --> 00:12:42,250
Just get it out of here!

265
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:44,875
Grotesque, you say?
I don't have to take this!

266
00:12:44,958 --> 00:12:46,083
There we go.

267
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:47,625
Now it's just as bad
as I thought it'd be!

268
00:12:47,708 --> 00:12:50,500
Okay everyone,
that's enough. Calm down.

269
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:53,166
[ICHIYA]
Mm! Man!

270
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:53,875
[KEMO-KEMO grunts]

271
00:12:53,958 --> 00:12:57,875
[CROWD screams]

272
00:12:57,958 --> 00:12:59,041
Kemo-Kemo!

273
00:12:59,125 --> 00:13:01,000
Did you just breathe
fire to protect me?

274
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:02,000
[KEMO-KEMO coos]

275
00:13:02,083 --> 00:13:04,250
Aww. You grew up so fast!

276
00:13:04,333 --> 00:13:05,500
Fun as this was,

277
00:13:05,583 --> 00:13:07,916
I think it's time for
you all to move along.

278
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:10,000
[LUCY]
Dangit, Natsu!

279
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:14,333
[KEMO-KEMO]
Sometimes, when I'm scared,

280
00:13:14,416 --> 00:13:18,083
I hear this sound in my head.
It makes it hard to think.

281
00:13:18,166 --> 00:13:21,333
It makes me do stuff I'd be
too scared to do without it.

282
00:13:21,416 --> 00:13:24,958
I wanted to protect my family.
I thought the sound would help.

283
00:13:25,041 --> 00:13:28,208
I was wrong. I made
things harder for Natsu.

284
00:13:28,291 --> 00:13:32,041
I hear these voices. Something
tells me I should listen.

285
00:13:40,291 --> 00:13:41,625
Looks weird.

286
00:13:41,708 --> 00:13:43,333
Having that in common,
I'm surprised he didn't know.

287
00:13:43,416 --> 00:13:46,000
All Gramps said is that I can't
keep him in the guild-hall.

288
00:13:46,083 --> 00:13:47,333
Just a couple o' days ago.

289
00:13:47,416 --> 00:13:49,291
The thing was even
smaller than Happy,

290
00:13:49,375 --> 00:13:51,250
and it doesn't eat or drink
so how's it growing?

291
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:52,541
Makarov's the biggest freak

292
00:13:52,625 --> 00:13:54,583
I've had the mixed
emotions of meeting.

293
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:57,500
If he's never seen it, then I
guess it's a new species.

294
00:13:57,583 --> 00:13:59,375
Want me to give it a spin?

295
00:13:59,458 --> 00:14:02,000
No thanks! We do appreciate
the offer though.

296
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:04,583
Why would Fairy Tail send
a lazy slacker like you,

297
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:05,791
instead of Juvia?

298
00:14:05,875 --> 00:14:07,666
I'm not here because
I wanna be, all right?

299
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:08,791
And if the bar's so high

300
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:10,791
then why aren't you
doin' the program?

301
00:14:10,875 --> 00:14:12,416
Such things are beneath me.

302
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:16,166
What could I possibly learn from
something so utterly juvenile?

303
00:14:18,708 --> 00:14:19,750
[ERZA]
Greetings.

304
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:21,125
[HAPPY]
So, whatcha got there?

305
00:14:21,208 --> 00:14:23,416
Stone tablets,
washed up from the sea.

306
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,875
My task is to decipher them,
but they're written in a tongue

307
00:14:25,958 --> 00:14:29,458
both foreign and ancient. Thus
your help would be invaluable.

308
00:14:33,708 --> 00:14:35,416
[LUCY] So, how does all
this stuff go together?

309
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,416
Certain passages from
these tablets can also

310
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:40,083
be found in this book.

311
00:14:40,166 --> 00:14:41,791
Here it is.

312
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:50,708
Hey, look. This picture.

313
00:14:50,791 --> 00:14:53,333
I also have this dictionary.
But the calligraphies

314
00:14:53,416 --> 00:14:55,250
are deviant, so it's
easy to confuse.

315
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:57,291
[LUCY groans]
We need Levy.

316
00:14:57,375 --> 00:14:59,541
Is there some way we
can get her over here?

317
00:14:59,625 --> 00:15:00,958
Not an option.

318
00:15:01,041 --> 00:15:03,125
As an aspiring novelist,
you're the best hope we have.

319
00:15:03,208 --> 00:15:05,291
I'll try to help but readin'
more than ten words

320
00:15:05,375 --> 00:15:07,083
at once makes my head hurt.

321
00:15:13,125 --> 00:15:15,541
Hey, Lucy? What can
I do to help out?

322
00:15:15,625 --> 00:15:16,291
[LUCY, HAPPY]
Go away.

323
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:18,166
That's just mean!

324
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:19,541
So. When's the big day?

325
00:15:19,625 --> 00:15:21,166
What are you talkin' about?

326
00:15:21,250 --> 00:15:24,166
You and Juvia's wedding
ceremony, what else?

327
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:27,083
We're not... engaged.
We're not even dating!

328
00:15:27,166 --> 00:15:29,666
Why would you ask that?
Don't you like her?

329
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:31,875
Which is precisely why
I value her happiness

330
00:15:31,958 --> 00:15:34,708
far above my own. As should you.

331
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,833
Stop making her
wait, Gray! A date!

332
00:15:38,916 --> 00:15:40,000
Pick one! Do it!

333
00:15:40,083 --> 00:15:43,791
Shut up! Get off my back!

334
00:15:43,875 --> 00:15:46,666
Be quiet! Lucy can't work
through your racket!

335
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:51,541
Let's see... That's "Sun."

336
00:15:51,625 --> 00:15:52,833
"Blessing."

337
00:15:52,916 --> 00:15:58,208
[KEMO-KEMO]
Wah... Oh? Wah?

338
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:00,125
[NATSU]
Hm?

339
00:16:00,208 --> 00:16:02,750
Hey, there's somethin' stuck
to the back of this tablet.

340
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,000
--[LUCY, HAPPY gasp]
--Is there, now?

341
00:16:04,083 --> 00:16:05,791
[LYON] You want it to be
a small, private affair?

342
00:16:05,875 --> 00:16:07,708
You're only inviting close
friends?! Are you not...

343
00:16:07,791 --> 00:16:09,416
[ERZA] Looks like a
cluster of sea shells.

344
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,125
Judging from the color,
they're fresh.

345
00:16:11,208 --> 00:16:13,500
Hush, will ya?
I can't hear myself think!

346
00:16:13,583 --> 00:16:16,125
If you don't shut up
over there, I'll spin you!

347
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:17,333
Making progress?

348
00:16:17,416 --> 00:16:19,750
I'm pretty sure that
this word means "tree."

349
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:23,833
Lemme think. There's a tree,
the sun, and a blessing,

350
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:26,166
which kinda makes me
think of photosynthesis.

351
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:29,000
But the picture shows people
running away from smoke.

352
00:16:29,083 --> 00:16:30,250
How does that tie in?

353
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:32,625
Indeed, this is
quite the conundrum.

354
00:16:32,708 --> 00:16:35,291
[GRAY] That's does it!
I've had enough outta you!

355
00:16:35,375 --> 00:16:37,541
[GRAY yells]

356
00:16:37,625 --> 00:16:39,500
[ALL yelp]

357
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:44,666
[LYON, GRAY]
Uh...

358
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:46,166
--You idiots!
--Why?

359
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:48,041
You coulda hurt someone!

360
00:16:48,125 --> 00:16:50,416
My. The vigor of
youth is astounding,

361
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:53,541
but since no one was hurt
and the tablets are fine--

362
00:16:53,625 --> 00:16:57,125
[screams]

363
00:16:59,791 --> 00:17:03,833
[JURA gasping]

364
00:17:03,916 --> 00:17:06,166
[ERZA, LUCY]
Uh...

365
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:08,750
Everything I've heard
about your guild is true!

366
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:10,375
Get out!

367
00:17:17,666 --> 00:17:20,041
[MILLIANNA]
Meow! Kitty-kitty! Meow!

368
00:17:20,125 --> 00:17:21,750
[KAGURA]
I... I missed you.

369
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,708
[HAPPY whimpering]

370
00:17:23,791 --> 00:17:25,041
[ERZA]
You missed me too?

371
00:17:25,125 --> 00:17:27,500
That's nothing to be ashamed of.
Say it loud! Aww.

372
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:29,125
Let it out and you'll
blush no more.

373
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:32,125
I missed you! Wow.

374
00:17:32,208 --> 00:17:34,375
That was completely
embarrassing.

375
00:17:34,458 --> 00:17:35,833
What, that shout
or the running leap

376
00:17:35,916 --> 00:17:38,708
into my arms before it?
We were even on the beach!

377
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:40,000
Never again.

378
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:43,125
Say, Millianna?

379
00:17:43,208 --> 00:17:45,416
Where did you come by
that massive slab of meat?

380
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,666
It's from a deep-sea
fish, they're huge.

381
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:49,416
How'd you catch it?

382
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,958
We didn't.

383
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:53,541
For reasons unknown, they've
been washing up along the shore.

384
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:55,166
We threw 'em on the
menu as a special

385
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:56,541
and now they're a trademark.

386
00:17:56,625 --> 00:17:57,916
Ooh.

387
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,833
Do you think you could spare
a bite for me, please?

388
00:17:59,916 --> 00:18:01,083
Yeah, no prob.

389
00:18:01,166 --> 00:18:03,125
But are you sure your
friends have got this?

390
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:10,041
[GRAY growl]

391
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:15,375
[GRAY]
Here!

392
00:18:15,458 --> 00:18:18,625
[CUSTOMERS scream]

393
00:18:18,708 --> 00:18:21,500
The service may be terrible,
but that drag is on point.

394
00:18:21,583 --> 00:18:24,125
Once I got their wigs on,
I was nearly fooled myself.

395
00:18:24,208 --> 00:18:25,250
Yeah, but if...

396
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:27,083
...someone... did notice...

397
00:18:27,166 --> 00:18:28,250
Right.

398
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:29,750
If word got out that
our girls-only guild

399
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:31,791
had been infiltrated
by the coarser sex.

400
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:33,291
It'd be a PR disaster.

401
00:18:33,375 --> 00:18:36,333
--[NATSU laughing]
--[LUCY grunting]

402
00:18:36,416 --> 00:18:38,541
I didn't order this swill!

403
00:18:38,625 --> 00:18:40,416
Screw this, I quit!

404
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:43,541
[CROWD screams]

405
00:18:44,416 --> 00:18:47,958
The guild's reputation will
never recover from this. Ever.

406
00:18:48,041 --> 00:18:50,458
Don't worry, I know the drill.
We'll be leaving now.

407
00:18:50,541 --> 00:18:52,666
Please do.

408
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:55,125
[BACCHUS]
Get wild!

409
00:18:55,208 --> 00:18:57,166
Wild!

410
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:58,666
[yelps]

411
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:00,791
It's not quite as impressive
when there's only two of ya.

412
00:19:00,875 --> 00:19:02,916
[ROCKER] Quatro Puppy has
changed its name back!

413
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,708
The wild boys are with
Quatro Cerberus once more.

414
00:19:05,791 --> 00:19:08,083
It's the only name that
feels right, really.

415
00:19:08,166 --> 00:19:09,916
Yeah, nobody asked
you about it, man.

416
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,250
Ah, crap.

417
00:19:11,333 --> 00:19:12,916
Your guild's got the only
chick that can keep up

418
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,791
with my drinkin,' but
instead of her, ya sent

419
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:15,958
a bunch of sober dudes!

420
00:19:16,041 --> 00:19:17,333
Sorry to disappoint.

421
00:19:17,416 --> 00:19:19,166
Take a hard, blurry look.
I'm all woman.

422
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:20,416
[laughs nervously]

423
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:23,083
Ah, well. I'll have to
do this different then.

424
00:19:23,166 --> 00:19:24,666
Hey! What are you playin' at?

425
00:19:24,750 --> 00:19:26,458
[NATSU groans]

426
00:19:26,541 --> 00:19:28,291
[growls]

427
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:29,666
I'm all fired up!

428
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:32,041
Hey. Why are you guys fighting?

429
00:19:32,125 --> 00:19:33,041
Just your run of the mill,

430
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:35,250
Quatro Cerberus
fightin' exercise!

431
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:37,083
It's on now!

432
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:40,791
[BACCHUS, NATSU yell]

433
00:19:40,875 --> 00:19:42,291
Cut it out! Both of you!

434
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:42,916
[LUCY]

435
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,666
[KEMO-KEMO yells]

436
00:19:49,291 --> 00:19:54,250
[NATSU, BACCHUS groaning]

437
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:56,666
[KEMO-KEMO]
Ah...

438
00:19:56,750 --> 00:19:59,083
[KEMO-KEMO] I think
I figured out my purpose.

439
00:19:59,166 --> 00:20:01,166
Natsu and Lucy are my family.

440
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:04,916
And that sound I hear:
it calls me to protect them.

441
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,791
But still, something
doesn't feel right.

442
00:20:07,875 --> 00:20:10,750
It's like I've forgotten
something really important.

443
00:20:10,833 --> 00:20:14,708
And no matter how hard
I try, I can't remember.

444
00:20:16,041 --> 00:20:18,666
[NATSU] I'm startin' to think
that you are a new species.

445
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:21,583
We've asked all over the place
and no one's got a clue.

446
00:20:21,666 --> 00:20:22,458
[KEMO-KEMO squeaks]

447
00:20:22,541 --> 00:20:24,250
Y'know. Who cares what ya are?

448
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:26,083
You're family,
and that's what matters.

449
00:20:26,166 --> 00:20:27,541
Ya got that right!

450
00:20:27,625 --> 00:20:29,791
Are either of you serious
about this exchange program?

451
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:31,166
Don't think we'd've
been kicked out

452
00:20:31,250 --> 00:20:33,416
of every single guild we've
been to if they were.

453
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:37,000
Hey, accidents happen.
We had fun. Who cares?

454
00:20:37,083 --> 00:20:38,708
Well, aren't you positive?

455
00:20:38,791 --> 00:20:40,833
Hey, Natsu!

456
00:20:40,916 --> 00:20:43,458
How's it goin' Sting?
Long time, no see.

457
00:20:43,541 --> 00:20:44,625
We've gotta hurry!

458
00:20:44,708 --> 00:20:46,125
They've cancelled
the exchange program!

459
00:20:46,208 --> 00:20:47,000
Huh?

460
00:20:47,083 --> 00:20:48,458
[LUCY gasps]

461
00:21:00,291 --> 00:21:00,958
That island.

462
00:21:01,041 --> 00:21:02,333
What about it?

463
00:21:02,416 --> 00:21:04,208
Is it not where it's supposed
to be or somethin'?

464
00:21:04,291 --> 00:21:05,750
It shouldn't be at all.

465
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:07,833
Popped out of the
ocean three days ago.

466
00:21:07,916 --> 00:21:09,750
Could it have been
an underwater volcano?

467
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:11,708
Islands don't just appear.

468
00:21:11,791 --> 00:21:13,333
I did consider that.

469
00:21:13,416 --> 00:21:15,458
Problem is, there's
already a forest on it.

470
00:21:15,541 --> 00:21:18,333
This island came into existence
with the full package.

471
00:21:18,416 --> 00:21:20,375
There was an earthquake
a few days ago.

472
00:21:20,458 --> 00:21:23,083
Might've been caused by this
island poofing into existence.

473
00:21:23,166 --> 00:21:25,333
Seems like a good guess to me.

474
00:21:25,416 --> 00:21:27,458
Hey, Lucy. Is that a building?

475
00:21:27,541 --> 00:21:28,875
I think it might be.

476
00:21:28,958 --> 00:21:32,250
So, we got this message
from the Magic Council.

477
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:34,750
[LAHAR] In it, we ask you
to survey this island.

478
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:36,250
[GRAY, NATSU, LUCY gasp]

479
00:21:38,208 --> 00:21:42,208
And do it together. Sabertooth
and Fairy Tail, as one.

480
00:21:42,291 --> 00:21:45,250
Came a long way to check
if they got your mail.

481
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:47,500
About that.
They kinda rode with us.

482
00:21:47,583 --> 00:21:49,791
The Master sent us
to check on you.

483
00:21:49,875 --> 00:21:52,375
Everywhere you've been,
mysterious stories of arson,

484
00:21:52,458 --> 00:21:54,875
vandalism, and restaurant
terrorism have followed.

485
00:21:54,958 --> 00:21:56,875
Mr. Lahar stopped by
the guild for a visit

486
00:21:56,958 --> 00:22:00,250
just before we left. So we
decided to come here together.

487
00:22:00,333 --> 00:22:02,375
If we're to form
the first expedition.

488
00:22:02,458 --> 00:22:04,916
Then you need tell us everything
you know about this island.

489
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,375
I don't plan to go in blindly.

490
00:22:07,458 --> 00:22:10,625
The Magic Council has
ordered me to tell you this.

491
00:22:10,708 --> 00:22:13,291
"The island is dangerous." So...

492
00:22:13,375 --> 00:22:14,541
That's it?

493
00:22:14,625 --> 00:22:15,916
[LUCY gasps]

494
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:18,750
[NATSU]
Hm. Hey! Is somethin' wrong?

495
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:25,250
[KEMO-KEMO] That important
thing that I've forgotten?

496
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:28,083
Sometimes I try too
hard to remember it.

497
